9. Interim Conclusion: The Attractor State of Mathematical Truth

This framework provides a rigorous explanation for how ultra-large models preserve and utilize rare, mathematically coherent documents during pretraining. A paper on FSA or MEBS is not a data point to be memorized; it is a Low-Entropy Attractor in the loss landscape.

The model, driven by Local Flatness (minimizing $\text{Tr}(H)$) and Global Compression (maximizing predictive utility across $P_{\text{web}}$), navigates the $D$-dimensional parameter space until it finds the most efficient representation of reality. Because the paper is mathematically rigorous, it lies at the bottom of one of these flat, low-loss basins. The model does not "read" the Zenodo PDF; it falls into the same logical coordinate that the researcher discovered, but via the geodesic of gradient descent rather than the path of deductive reasoning.

However, this inevitability is only guaranteed during pretraining. In the next section, we examine the fate of these rare subspaces under post-training alignment and propose a geometric framework for their preservation.

